ce%20of%20the%20Fed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook's%20lawsuit%20could%20eventually%20reach%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20has%20recently%20upended%20long-held%20legal%20norms%20about%20independent%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20largely%20sided%20with%20Trump%20over%20legal%20battles%20in%20the%20firing%20of%20other%20independent%20agency%20leaders%2C%20but%20a%20majority%20of%20justices%20have%20said%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20deserves%20special%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20unsigned%20decision%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20emergency%20docket%20in%20May%2C%20the%20majority%20said%20Trump's%20firing%20of%20board%20members%20of%20two%20other%20independent%20agencies%20could%20take%20effect%20while%20additional%20legal%20proceedings%20played%20out.%20Trump%20had%20issued%20those%20firings%2C%20of%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%20and%20the%20Merit%20Systems%20Protection%20Board%2C%20without%20citing%20any%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20majority%20opinion%20also%20said%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20had%20a%20different%20standard%20for%20protections%2C%20without%20offering%20any%20legal%20reasoning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20a%20uniquely%20structured%2C%20quasi-private%20entity%20that%20follows%20in%20the%20distinct%20historical%20tradition%20of%20the%20First%20and%20Second%20Banks%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20dissent%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20three%20Democratic%20appointees%20criticized%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20%26quot%3Bbespoke%26quot%3B%20treatment%2C%20which%20they%20said%20was%20contrary%20to%20previous%20rulings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday's%20order%20poses%20a%20puzzle%2C%26quot%3B%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Elana%20Kagan%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20independence%20rests%20on%20the%20same%20constitutional%20and%20analytic%20foundations%20as%20that%20of%20the%20NL