%20be%20defined%20in%20different%20ways%2C%20but%20it%20generally%20refers%20to%20using%20plain%20English%20to%20instruct%20AI%20tools%20to%20write%20code.%20The%20phenomenon%20has%20swept%20through%20the%20tech%20world%2C%20calling%20into%20question%20the%20wisdom%20of%20the%20widespread%20career%20advice%20that%20simply%20said%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-research-head-career-advice-learn-to-code-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elearn%20to%20code%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20engineers%20at%20major%20tech%20companies%20and%20computer%20science%20professors%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20while%20AI%20can%20make%20coding%20faster%20and%20more%20fun%2C%20it's%20no%20replacement%20for%20software%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20sort%20of%20like%20giving%20a%20novice%20driver%20a%20race%20car%2C%26quot%3B%20Nenad%20Medvidovic%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Computer%20Science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20certain%20things%20that%20can%20go%20very%20wrong%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20you're%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedvidovic%20said%20studies%20show%20that%20AI%20works%20well%20for%20easier%20or%20moderately%20complex%20pieces%20of%20code%2C%20but%20that%20once%20you%20give%20it%20more%20complex%20problems%2C%20%26quot%3Bvibe%20coding%20becomes%20less%20useful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22565c1572-6913-432d-87b7-9fd5520e4128%5C%22%3ECoding%20with%20AI%20has%20its%20limits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20AI%20could%20already%20be%20affecting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheres-more-bad-news-for-entry-level-coders-ai-study-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eentry-level%20coding%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Researchers%20at%20Stanford%20found%20in%20a%20new%20study%20that%20in%20the%20most%20AI-exposed%20professions%2C%20which%20they%20said%20included%20software%20engineers%2C%20workers%20ages%2022%20to%2025%20saw%20a%2013%25%20relative%20decline%20in%20employment%20since%20the%20widespread%20adoption%20of%20generative%20AI.%20Employment%20for%20early%20career%20software%20developers%20declined%20by%20nearly%2020%25%20from%20its%20peak%20in%20late%202022%20to%20July%202025%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Millstein%2C%20a%20computer%20scientist%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20said%20coding%20with%20AI%20is%20similar%20to%20coding%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgithub-ceo-hiring-junior-engineers-interns-important-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejunior%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20give%20it%20instructions%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20you%20try%20this%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20you%20might%20review%20it%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20part%20is%20good%2C%20but%20try%20doing%20this%20part%20differently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20a%20long%20way%20from%20the%20common%20misconceptions%20of%20vibe%20coding%2C%20where%20the%20person%20doing%20it%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20understand%20code%2C%20and%20the%20AI%20can%20handle%20a%20project%20from%20beginning%20to%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20reading%20the%20code.%20You're%20responsible%20for%20the%20code%2C%26quot%3B%20Millstein%20said%20of%20engineers%20using%20AI%20tools.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20sometimes%20there%20are%20parts%20that%20are%20just%20too%20tricky%20or%20would%20be%20too%20complicated%20to%20explain%20to%20the%20AI%2C%20and%20so%20you%20end%20up%20doing%20it%20yourself%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillstein%20said%20the%20initial%20code%20creation%20is%20also%20a%20small%20part%20of%20the%20software%20cycle%20%E2%80%94%20it%20also%20needs%20to%20be%20maintained%20and%20has%20to%20have%20bug%20fixes%20and%20extensions%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20definitely%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20what%20a%20software%20engineer%20is%20doing%20or%20needs%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20systems%20our%20world%20depends%20on%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ai-could-transform-investment-banking-wealth-management-2030-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20institutions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20healthcare%2C%20medicine%20%E2%80%94%20the%20stakes%20are%20simply%20too%20high%20to%20trust%20AI-generated%20code%20without%20a%20person%20who%20actually%20understands%20the%20code%2C%20security%20requirements%2C%20and%20how%20it%20interacts%20with%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJigar%20Bhati%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-software-engineer-how-to-get-hired-work-experience-twitter-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eengineer%20at%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20AI%20tools%20act%20more%20as%20an%20assistant%20rather%20than%20automating%20the%20process%20of%20coding.%20As%20the%20human%20engineer%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20still%20in%20control.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20said%20that%20vibe%20coding%20can%20be%20useful%20for%20creating%20a%20quick%20prototype%20or%20proof%20of%20concept%2C%20but%20to%20be%20a%20usable%20product%2C%20it%20requires%20experienced%20engineers%20with%20a%20critical%20understanding%20of%20how%20the%20system%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20there's%20still%20an%20aspect%20of%2C%20you%20need%20to%20talk%20to%2010%20different%20teams%20to%20make%20a%20great%20product%2C%20and%20that%20is%20something%20software%20engineers%20are%20involved%20in%20day-to-day%20life%20as%20well%2C%20apart%20from%20just%20coding%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERitvika%20Nagula%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-senior-software-engineer-s