stors%20to%20get%20access%20to%20theoretically%20attractive%20AI%20assets%2C%20and%20those%20will%20trade%20at%20a%20premium.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20see%20AI%20companies%20trading%20at%2050%20or%20100%20times%20revenues%2C%20or%20raising%20rounds%20at%20that%2C%20what's%20the%20end%20game%3F%20If%20you're%20eventually%20valued%20in%20the%20public%20market%20at%20five%20to%2010%20times%20revenue%2C%20you%20have%20to%20grow%20dramatically%20to%20overcome%20that%20valuation%20reduction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBesides%20the%20means%20of%20investment%20in%20AI%2C%20what%20other%20indicators%20are%20there%20that%20we're%20headed%20into%20an%20AI%20bubble%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20general%20signals%20of%20bubbles%2C%20and%20they've%20been%20relatively%20prevalent%20across%20the%20different%20hype%20cycles%20in%20tech.%201)%20a%20rapid%20increase%20in%20valuations%2C%202)%20the%20increasing%20frequency%20of%20new%20funding%20rounds%2C%203)%20investors%20investing%20in%20the%20greater%20fool%20theory%2C%20or%20investing%20based%20on%20expectations%20of%20what%20other%20investors%20are%20going%20to%20do%2C%20versus%20fundamentals%2C%20and%20then%204)%20increases%20in%20prices%20based%20upon%20fundamental%20metrics%2C%20so%20things%20like%20price%20to%20revenue%2C%20price%20to%20earnings%2C%20etc%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20valuation%20went%20from%20%24300%20billion%20in%20the%20last%20round%20to%20%24500%20billion%20in%20their%20tender%20offer.%20It's%20quite%20rare%20for%20a%20private%20company%20to%20be%20valued%20at%20even%20%24100%20million.%20Now%20you%20have%20companies%20valued%20at%20much%20more%20than%20that%20and%20increasing%20their%20valuations%20within%20periods%20of%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20biggest%20companies%20are%20valued%20at%20a%20much%20larger%20percentage%20of%20the%20public%20markets%2C%20they%20can%20influence%20the%20performance%20of%20those%20markets%20over%20the%20long%20term.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-bubble-magnificent-seven-terrific-20-sp500-valuations-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMagnificent%20Seven%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they're%20not%20valued%20at%20extremely%20high%20multiples%20of%20earnings%2C%20but%20you%20do%20see%20their%20capital%20expenditures%20going%20up%20dramatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20estimated%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wheresyoured.at%2Fthe-haters-gui%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24560%20billion%20has%20been%20invested%20in%20capex%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20versus%20the%20roughly%20%2435%20billion%20of%20revenues%20generated%20by%20that%20spend.%20OpenAI%20is%20about%20%2410%20billion%20of%20this%2C%20which%20is%20them%20basically%20buying%20Microsoft%20Azure%20and%20services.%20So%20you%20discount%20that%20a%20little%20bit%20because%20Microsoft%20is%20selling%20that%20at%20cost.%20There's%20a%20massive%20disconnect%20between%20capex%20spending%20and%20the%20revenue%20generated%20by%20that%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20big%20concentration%20of%20the%20public%20market%20in%20these%20companies%2C%20changes%20to%20their%20spending%20may%20cause%20a%20chain%20reaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20also%20see%20certain%20public%20companies%20trading%20at%20very%20high%20multiples%20of%20revenue.%20One%20is%20Palantir.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-stock-prcue-short-valuation-openai-shares-andrew-left-citron-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIt's%20trading%20at%20over%20100%20times%20its%20revenues%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20quite%20extreme%20and%20rare.%20Palantir's%20a%20great%20company%2C%20but%20when%20you%20start%20to%20look%20at%20those%20multiples%2C%20you%20say%2C%20'Hmm%2C%20that's%20reminiscent%20of%20previous%20bubble%20periods.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20your%20conclusion%20about%20an%20AI%20bubble%20is%20right%2C%20what%20might%20we%20